Package model

Class Inventory

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.Inventory
  • public class Inventory
extends java.lang.Object
    The Inventory class simulates an Inventory. It allows for Parts and Products to be added, removed, searched for, and managed within the Inventory.
    Author:
    Mary Williams

    • Method Detail

      • addPart

        public static void addPart​(Part newPart)
        The addPart method adds a Part to the allParts Observable List. It also adds 1 to the totalPartsEver static int to count all Parts for use in the unique ID.
        Parameters:
        newPart - The part to be added to the allParts Observable List.

      • addProduct

        public static void addProduct​(Product newProduct)
        The addProduct method adds a Product to the allProducts Observable List. It also adds 1 to the totalProductsEver static int to count all Products for use in the unique ID.
        Parameters:
        newProduct - The product to be added to the allProducts Observable List.

      • lookupPart

        public static Part lookupPart​(int partId)
        The lookupPart method that accepts an int parameter searches the allParts Observable List for a Part where the ID matches the parameter.
        Parameters:
        partId - The integer to look for in allParts part IDs.
        Returns:
        If a part ID matches in the search it returns the part, otherwise it returns null if no part ID matches or if there are no parts in the allParts Observable List to search from.

      • lookupProduct

        public static Product lookupProduct​(int productId)
        The lookupProduct method that accepts an int parameter searches the allProducts Observable List for a Product where the ID matches the parameter.
        Parameters:
        productId - The integer to look for in allProducts product IDs.
        Returns:
        If a product ID matches in the search it returns the product, otherwise it returns null if no product ID matches or if there are no products in the allProducts Observable List to search from.

      • lookupPart

        public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<Part> lookupPart​(java.lang.String partName)
        The lookupPart method that accepts a string parameter searches the allParts Observable List for all Part names that contain a matching string to the parameter.
        Parameters:
        partName - The string to check against allParts part names.
        Returns:
        The list of all Parts where the name contains the search string even if none are found, otherwise it returns null if there are no parts in the allParts Observable List to search from.

      • lookupProduct

        public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<Product> lookupProduct​(java.lang.String productName)
        The lookupProduct method that accepts a string parameter searches the allProducts Observable List for all Product names that contain a matching string to the parameter.
        Parameters:
        productName - The string to check against allProducts product names.
        Returns:
        The list of all Products where the name contains the search string even if none are found, otherwise it returns null if there are no products in the allProducts Observable List to search from.

      • updatePart

        public static void updatePart​(int index,
                              Part selectedPart)
        The updatePart method replaces a Part in the allParts Observable List.
        Parameters:
        index - The index of the part in the allParts Observable List to replace.
        selectedPart - The updated part to replace its older version in the allParts Observable List.

      • updateProduct

        public static void updateProduct​(int index,
                                 Product newProduct)
        The updateProduct method replaces a Product in the allProducts Observable List.
        Parameters:
        index - The index of the product in the allProducts Observable List to replace.
        newProduct - The updated product to replace its older version in the allProducts Observable List.

      • deletePart

        public static boolean deletePart​(Part selectedPart)
        The deletePart method removes a Part from the allParts Observable List.
        Parameters:
        selectedPart - The part to be removed from the allParts Observable List.
        Returns:
        If the selectedPart can be removed from the allParts Observable List it returns true, otherwise it returns false.

      • deleteProduct

        public static boolean deleteProduct​(Product selectedProduct)
        The deleteProduct method removes a Product from the allProducts Observable List, as long as it has no associated Parts.
        Parameters:
        selectedProduct - The product to be removed from the allProducts Observable List.
        Returns:
        If the selectedProduct can be removed from the allProducts Observable List it returns true, otherwise it returns false.
